(18,14,8,2,'Laravel 12 for Beginners','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5kCN0QEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','9798298252201',6500,'Laravel 12 for Beginners: Build Modern Web Apps with PHP the Easy Way Learning to code can feel overwhelming-especially when faced with complex tutorials that assume you already know the basics. If you\'ve ever felt intimidated by programming or wondered if web development is \"too hard\" for you, this book is here to prove the opposite. With Laravel 12 for Beginners, you\'ll discover that creating modern, professional web applications with PHP can be straightforward, approachable, and even fun. This book is written for absolute beginners. You don\'t need prior coding experience, a technical background, or advanced math skills. Instead, you\'ll get a step-by-step, supportive guide that explains every concept in plain language, backed by practical examples that build your confidence as you go. Each chapter is designed to make progress feel achievable, normalize mistakes as part of the process, and celebrate every small win along the way. Inside, you\'ll learn how to: Set up your development environment and install Laravel 12 without frustration. Understand the building blocks of modern web apps-from routes and controllers to models and views. Work with databases the easy way using Laravel\'s powerful Eloquent ORM. Build interactive forms, handle user input, and validate data securely. Add authentication and authorization to protect your app with ease. Deploy your finished projects online and share them with the world. What makes this book different is its friendly, confidence-building approach. Instead of rushing through theory, you\'ll work through real-world examples and small projects that show you how Laravel is used in practice. By the end, you\'ll have the practical skills to build apps you\'re proud of-and the mindset to keep learning without fear. Whether you dream of launching your own projects, b