(23,18,5,2,'Practical Laravel 5','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CjYC0QEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','9781484202487',1700,'Build a fully-fledged, feature-rich application from scratch using Laravel. You\'ll learn by doing, not simply studying. At the end of each step, not only will you have learned a new skill, trick or technique – but you\'ll have built another feature of your first hand-crafted Laravel application. You\'ll go beyond the Laravel framework itself as we take a look at some of the skills any professional developer needs, to take your career – or indeed hobby – to the next level. Simple to grasp yet incredibly powerful, Laravel is attracting enormous attention from beginners and experienced developers alike for its expressiveness and versatility. This book will show you what\'s got people so excited. Packed with tips, tricks and tools of the trade, Practical Laravel 5 gives you everything you need to develop sophisticated web applications using this exciting new framework. What You\'ll Learn Know when Laravel is the right tool for your project Have a solid understanding of the framework\'s major features Possess the knowledge and confidence to build a production-ready application – from scratch Have a broad awareness of relevant tools, techniques and processes Be able to launch your applications into the cloud Who This Book Is For Practical Laravel 5 is for novice through to intermediate developers new to Laravel',19,1,'2019-03-07','2025-12-29 11:50:56','2025-12-29 11:50:56'),
(24,19,8,2,'Laravel 12 for Modern Web Development','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0bal0QEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','9798270389048',9800,'Building secure, scalable, and high-performance web applications shouldn\'t feel like wrestling complexity, it should feel like craftsmanship. Yet most developers still waste hours trying to piece together outdated tutorials, fragile boilerplates, and scattered documentation. Laravel 12 for Modern Web Development fixes that problem completely. This book gives you everything you need to master the newest version of Laravel from project setup to real-world deployment so you can confidently build production-grade applications that scale. It\'s not another surface-level walkthrough; it\'s a full professional guide that reflects how Laravel 12 is actually used in modern teams today. You\'ll start with the essentials: environment setup, starter kits, authentication, and secure configuration. Then you\'ll move through advanced Laravel 12 concepts like Eloquent optimization, queues and caching, server-side rendering with Inertia, Livewire interactivity, and integration with WorkOS AuthKit for SSO and passkeys. Every chapter is structured as a practical tutorial that mirrors real development challenges, showing you exactly how to apply each concept in a working project. By the end of the book, you won\'t just understand Laravel-you\'ll think like a Laravel developer. You\'ll know how to: Build full-stack applications using React, Vue, or Livewire starter kits with Laravel 12. Secure authentication using WorkOS, 2FA, and email verification. Design clean Eloquent models and handle complex relationships efficiently. Implement caching, queues, and Laravel Octane for performance at scale. Deploy production-ready apps using Docker, Forge, or Vapor with CI/CD automation. Maintain, test, and upgrade Laravel applications with zero downtime. Throughout, you\'ll follow two complete case studies, a School Managem