g both webpack and Nuxt.js templates while exploring cool hot Nuxt.js features such as code splitting and server-side rendering. We will use Jest to test this application, and we will even revive some trigonometry from our secondary school!While developing the app, you will go through the new grid system of Bootstrap 4 along with Vue.js\' directives. We will connect Vuex store to the Firebase real-time database, data storage, and authentication APIs and use this data later inside the application\'s reactive components. Finally, we will quickly deploy our application using the Firebase hosting mechanism.Style and ApproachStep-by-step tutorial',20,1,'2017-09-28','2025-12-29 11:51:03','2025-12-29 11:51:03'),
